WEAZL33.original: Francis McReary, witnessed the murder of his elder brother
WEAZL33.translated: Francis McReary亲眼目睹哥哥遇害
英雄警察目睹哥哥被杀

WEAZL33.original: Although Mr. McReary has never tried to hide his tough Dukes upbringing, nor a family background with links to organized crime, he himself has always stood tall as a community leader and we mourn with him in this time of sorrow.
WEAZL33.translated: 虽然McReary先生从未掩盖过他在Dukes的艰苦成长环境，也没有掩盖他那与黑社会有关联的家庭背景，但他一直是社区的榜样与领袖。此时此刻，让我们与他一起默哀。

WEAZL33.original: Deputy Police Commissioner, Francis McReary, witnessed the murder of his elder brother in Algonquin. His brother Derrick was assassinated by a sniper while the two men enjoyed a catch up in a city park. Francis McReary has risen through the ranks of the police force and been a vocal proponent of law and order throughout difficult times for the city. He has strongly denied spurious allegations made against him.
WEAZL33.translated: 警局副局长Francis McReary目击了他哥哥在Algonquin遇害的过程。当时他们兄弟二人在公园里感人重逢，随后他的哥哥Derrick被一名狙击手暗杀。Francis McReary在警局内平步青云，在本市的困难时期仍坚持拥护法律与秩序。他坚决否认那些对他发起的虚假指控。
